onising particles, improving on previous work at ELBE\nand exceeding the NeuLAND timing goal of $\\sigma_t$ < 150 ps. Over a range of\n10-300 MeV deposited energy in the NeuLAND bar, the gain was found to deviate\nby $\\leq$10% ($\\leq$20%) from linearity for 35 mm (75 mm) SiPM pitch,\nrespectively, satisfactory for calorimetric use of the full NeuLAND detector.\nThe dark rate of the prototype studied was found to be lower than the expected\ncosmic-ray induced background in NeuLAND.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 Dec 2022 12:55:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-11"}
